The Minister of Agriculture and Natural Resources, Mohammed Sabo Nanono has disclosed that the Federal Executive Council has approved a contract of N244 million for the purchase of raw materials for the production of vaccines for use against animal diseases.  Briefing state House Correspondents after the weekly FEC meeting at the Presidential Villa in Abuja, the Minister said the memorandum for the supply of inputs for vaccines production and research for National Veterinary Research Institute at Vom was presented to the council. The Minister of Works and Housing, Babatunde Fashola said two memoranda were presented towards achieving the objective of completing some of the inherited roads from previous administration. 